{"key":"processedPost-16369317","value":{"id":16369317,"first":16367767,"last":16369429,"when":1339505013,"utime":"06/12/12 03:43 PM","cleanedPost":"Wheat and oat bran work fine.&nbsp; Don't use whole wheat flour from the grocery store because it's usually just white flour with a tiny amount of whole wheat added to make it look brown.&nbsp; They shouldn't even be able to call it whole wheat but they do.<br />As already said, simply buy a large bag of brown rice and grind it in a coffee grinder.&nbsp; Health food stores sell rice bran in the refrigerated section and that's great.&nbsp; Another option is to go to a feed store and get a large bag of rice bran for horses as shown below.&nbsp; It's what I use for <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek</a> and also as a supplement for sawdust substrates for our <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Mountain-Mushroom-Farm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shiitake mushroom farm.</a><br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/09-15/920738766-Rice_Bran_for_Horses_001.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/09-15/920738766-thumb_Rice_Bran_for_Horses_001.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/09-15/920738861-Rice_Bran_for_Horses_002.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/09-15/920738861-thumb_Rice_Bran_for_Horses_002.jpg\"></a>"}}